	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>July 21 1863</date>.</p>
				<p>Rev. &#38; dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I beg to acknowledge<lb/> the receipt of your note of <date>Friday</date>&#44;<lb/> authorizing me to call a meeting of<lb/> the Executive Committee of the Board of<lb/> Delegates&#44; but expressing your inability to<lb/> be present.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">As for my part&#44; I deem<lb/> it advisable that you should preside&#44;<lb/> if possible&#44; at the meeting and as<lb/> three or more of the Committee are<lb/> out of town &#38; I shall myself leave<lb/> to <sic>morrow</sic> for a fortnight&#39;s trip&#44; I<lb/> have concluded to adopt your<lb/> alternative and wait until the first<lb/> or second week in <date>August</date> to<lb/> summon a meeting.  I leave it to<lb/> you to name the day.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Wishing you a</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>pleasant trip to <placeName>Washington</placeName>&#44;<lb/> in which father joins<add>&#63;</add>&#44; I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">dear sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Very Truly Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">M. J. Isaacs</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
		</body>
